100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On February 12, 1926, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, addressing ongoing global tensions and the challenges of disarmament. In the United States, the Senate continued debates over the McNary-Haugen Bill, aimed at supporting struggling farmers through government price supports. Meanwhile, Italy's Mussolini solidified his grip on power, emphasizing his regime's commitment to national strength and expansion.
